attachments.title: Commander 1v1 Banned Update
attachments.text: Announcement: June 13, 2017 Effective Date: June 14, 2017 (with the downtime) Next Announcement: July 5, 2017 No changes. Commander 1v1′s ban list is stiill in “rapid iteration”, where changes can be made outside of the normal banned and restricted schedule for a new format. Looking at the current format data on Magic Online, however, R&D determined the metagame is continuing to shift and evolve, and wants this to keep playing out more rather than disrupt it with a banned list change. Unfortunately, when the initial banned list was implemented, two cards on the list mistakenly did not have their banning implemented. We are going to use the June 14 downtime to correct this, so Commander 1v1 leagues will be reset during tomorrow’s downtime. Standard leagues will also be reset during that downtime as Aetherworks Marvel was banned in Standard.  Constructed leagues in formats other than Standard and Commander 1v1 will be extended until July 10 (just before Hour of Devastation events begin). Happy Commandering! - Lee

attachments.title: StarCityGames.com - Commander 2017: Going Tribal
attachments.text: Bennie Smith gives his thoughts on Commander 2017 containing four "tribal" decks. Then he shares a Samut, Voice of Dissent list! Abilities for all!

text: That's the article he referenced

I agree with the article quite a bit. The decks are made to be played against each other, so Coat of Arms and Patriarch's Bidding and such are very unlikely to be printed here. 

I also happen to disagree with the "all five color decks" idea. Four is a weird number but i think they just wanted flexibility, rather than the obligation of a cycle. They don't like making cycles of things unless they have to, and with tribal, they don't have to. So I bet we'll see a bunch of weird stuff, with some colors getting a little more representation than others. (Two 5-color and two colorless would be neat, though.)

If we're trying to guess the tribes, I think the best indicator is that wizards now uses Commander sets to fill holes. Characters like Gisa and Geralf didn't have cards until C15. We had a Taigam character spoiled just recently too, and he was a huge hole in design. Beyond the story, they might try to fill in holes for tribes that don't have a specific commander to lead them already. (To my mind, this disqualifies zombies, elves, goblins, and especially allies and silvers, since those already all have obvious leaders for tribe-focused decks.) Angels, for example, don't have a specific legend who cares about angel tribal. Those are the kinds of commanders I think we're more likely to see.
